---
/**
 * Players Guide - Quick Start (main landing page)
 */
import GuideLayout from '../../layouts/GuideLayout.astro';
import Button from '../../components/Button.astro';
---

<GuideLayout title="Quick Start Guide" currentPage="quick-start" description="Get started playing on BlockHaven Minecraft server">
  <section id="quick-start">
    <h1>Quick Start Guide</h1>
    <p class="text-xl !text-text-light mb-8">
      Welcome to BlockHaven! This guide will help you get started on your adventure.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-primary-gold/10 border border-primary-gold/30 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
      <h3 class="!mt-0 !text-primary-gold">New to Minecraft?</h3>
      <p class="!mb-0">
        If you're completely new to Minecraft, check out our <a href="/guide/basics">Minecraft Basics</a> guide first.
        It covers everything from your first night to crafting essential tools.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="connecting">
    <h2>Step 1: Connect to the Server</h2>
    <p>
      BlockHaven supports both <strong>Java Edition</strong> and <strong>Bedrock Edition</strong>,
      so you can play from PC, console, or mobile.
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-secondary-stone/10 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-text-light mb-2">Java Edition</h4>
        <code class="text-lg">play.bhsmp.com</code>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-secondary-stone/10 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-text-light mb-2">Bedrock Edition</h4>
        <code class="text-lg">play.bhsmp.com:19132</code>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p>
      Need detailed connection instructions? Visit our <a href="/connect">How to Connect</a> page,
      which includes step-by-step guides and console workarounds.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="spawn-hub">
    <h2>Step 2: Explore the Spawn Hub</h2>
    <p>
      When you first join BlockHaven, you'll arrive at the <strong>Spawn Hub</strong> - a central area
      that connects all our worlds. From here, you can:
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Walk through portals</strong> to travel to different worlds</li>
      <li><strong>Read signs and information boards</strong> to learn about each world</li>
      <li><strong>Access community resources</strong> to help you get started</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="starter-kit">
    <h2>Step 3: Get Your Starter Kit</h2>
    <p>
      When you enter any Survival world for the first time, you'll automatically receive a <strong>Starter Kit</strong>
      containing essential supplies to help you begin your adventure:
    </p>

    <div class="bg-secondary-stone/10 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h4 class="font-semibold text-text-light mb-3">Starter Kit Contents:</h4>
      <ul class="!mb-0">
        <li><strong>Golden Shovel</strong> - Used for claiming land (right-click two corners to claim)</li>
        <li><strong>Basic Tools</strong> - Stone pickaxe, axe, and sword to get you started</li>
        <li><strong>Food</strong> - Enough food to survive your first day</li>
        <li><strong>Torches</strong> - Light up your first shelter</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="safe-zone">
    <h2>Step 4: Know Your Safe Zones</h2>
    <p>
      Each Survival world has a <strong>safe zone</strong> around the spawn area where mobs and monsters
      cannot deal damage to players. This is especially helpful if you happen to spawn into a world at night!
    </p>

    <div class="bg-accent-diamond/10 border border-accent-diamond/30 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
      <h4 class="!mt-0 text-accent-diamond">Pro Tip</h4>
      <p class="!mb-0">
        If it's nighttime when you spawn and you're not ready to face monsters yet,
        stay within the safe zone until dawn. You can use this time to check out the area
        and plan where you want to build.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="first-steps">
    <h2>Step 5: Your First Survival Steps</h2>
    <p>
      Once you venture out of the safe zone into the wilderness, here's what to do:
    </p>

    <ol>
      <li>
        <strong>Find a good spot</strong> - Look for an area you'd like to call home.
        Consider proximity to resources, water, and interesting terrain.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Claim your land</strong> - Use your <strong>golden shovel</strong> to claim the area.
        Right-click one corner, then right-click the opposite corner. You can also use
        <code>/claim auto</code> to claim as you walk.
        <a href="/guide/land-claims">Learn more about land claims</a>.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Set your home</strong> - Type <code>/sethome</code> to save your location.
        You can return anytime with <code>/home</code>.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Join a job</strong> - Earn money by doing what you love!
        Type <code>/jobs browse</code> to see available jobs.
        <a href="/guide/economy">Learn more about jobs & economy</a>.
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section id="essential-commands">
    <h2>Essential Commands</h2>
    <p>Here are the most important commands to get you started:</p>

    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Command</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/sethome</code></td>
          <td>Save your current location as home</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/home</code></td>
          <td>Teleport back to your home</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/spawn</code></td>
          <td>Return to the world spawn point</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/tpa [player]</code></td>
          <td>Request to teleport to another player</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/tpaccept</code></td>
          <td>Accept a teleport request</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/bal</code></td>
          <td>Check your money balance</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/jobs browse</code></td>
          <td>View available jobs</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/mvtp [world]</code></td>
          <td>Teleport to a specific world</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section id="next-steps">
    <h2>Next Steps</h2>
    <p>Now that you know the basics, explore these guides to learn more:</p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-6">
      <a href="/guide/basics" class="block bg-secondary-stone/10 hover:bg-secondary-stone/20 rounded-xl p-6 transition-colors no-underline">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-text-light mb-2">Minecraft Basics</h4>
        <p class="text-sm !mb-0">New to Minecraft? Learn the fundamentals from gathering resources to surviving your first night.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/guide/land-claims" class="block bg-secondary-stone/10 hover:bg-secondary-stone/20 rounded-xl p-6 transition-colors no-underline">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-text-light mb-2">Land Claims</h4>
        <p class="text-sm !mb-0">Protect your builds from griefing with our land claiming system.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/guide/economy" class="block bg-secondary-stone/10 hover:bg-secondary-stone/20 rounded-xl p-6 transition-colors no-underline">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-text-light mb-2">Jobs & Economy</h4>
        <p class="text-sm !mb-0">Earn money, join jobs, and trade with other players.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/guide/worlds" class="block bg-secondary-stone/10 hover:bg-secondary-stone/20 rounded-xl p-6 transition-colors no-underline">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-text-light mb-2">Worlds & Travel</h4>
        <p class="text-sm !mb-0">Learn about our different worlds and how to travel between them.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</GuideLayout>
